  "prompt": "Which is correct, \"queue the music\" or \"cue the music,\" and why?",
  "response": "The correct phrase is \"cue the music.\" In this context, \"cue\" means to signal or prompt something to start, such as music playing in a performance or production. \"Queue,\" on the other hand, refers to a line or sequence of items waiting to be processed or a waiting line itself, and it does not apply in this situation. Therefore, when you want to instruct someone to begin the music, you would say \"cue the music.\"",
